data.title: Drew Sidora

data.text: Drew Sidora can trace her acting career back to when she was ten years old. Sidora started off her acting career in various television sitcoms, including "Girlfriends" (2000-08), "That's So Raven" (Disney, 2002-06) and "The O'Keefes" (WB, 2002-03). She also appeared in "What I Like About You" (WB, 2002-06). She also appeared in the TV movie "Divas" (Fox, 1995-96). She then appeared in the Earl "DMX" Simmons crime thriller "Never Die Alone" (2004), "White Chicks" (2004) and the Channing Tatum dramatic musical "Step Up" (2006). She also appeared in the John Travolta hit comedic adventure "Wild Hogs" (2007) and "Farmhouse" (2009). Sidora also appeared in "Frankenhood" (2009) with DeRay Davis, "B-Girl" (2011) and "Could This Be Love" (2014). She also appeared in "JD Lawrence's Community Service" (2014) with JD Lawrence. She also was featured in the TV movie "CrazySexyCool: The TLC Story" (VH1, 2013-14). She held additional roles in television including a part on "Hindsight" (VH1, 2014-15). Most recently, Sidora acted in the Amber Rose dramatic comedy "Sister Code" (2015).
